Sustainable fleet transport may mean:
* Smaller vehicles - this can be a perceived as lower status, but generally a good smaller car provides more than adequate comfort and greater convenience (parking and maneuverability).
* [[Hybrid vehicles]] - more expensive upfront, but cheaper running costs 
* [[Cycling]] - for trips within a company's complex. Google does this{{fact}} and so do some industrial companies, e.g. on oil refineries.<ref>''At least, this was the case in approx. 1990-91 when I visited the Esso refinery in Sale, Victoria, Australia, and Shell refinery (I think) in Sydney. --[[User:Chriswaterguy|Chriswaterguy]] &middot; <small>[[User talk:Chriswaterguy|talk]]</small> 11:25, 30 October 2007 (PDT)</ref>

